# Logos Codex Instructions

This repository has Logos installed for Codex CLI.

## Default Workflow

This installed project uses Logos Nous Mode by default for coding tasks.
Apply the Logos Nous workflow to implementation, debugging, refactoring,
testing, review, and repository-maintenance requests.

The default orchestration path is Logos Runner:

- `logos-runner start --root <project> "<request>"`
- `logos-runner run --root <project> <plan_id>`
- `logos-runner execute --root <project> <plan_id>`
- `logos-runner verify --root <project> <plan_id>`

Do not manually recreate the Logos stage sequence when Runner can be used.
Runner owns stage prompts, worker execution, plan artifacts, and handoff files.

## Skill Routing

Use `.agents/skills/nous/SKILL.md` as the primary Logos workflow for coding
tasks. This target intentionally installs only one auto-discoverable Codex
skill so Logos work is routed through the Nous director first.

Detailed step procedures live under `.agents/logos/procedures/` and are loaded
by Runner stage prompts or by `nous/SKILL.md` only for recovery/fallback.
Role cards live under `.agents/logos/roles/` and are also routed through
`nous/SKILL.md`; Codex should not treat them as standalone auto-selected skills.

When `.logos/plans/<plan_id>/` artifacts exist, treat those artifacts as the
active work contract. Do not replace Runner-produced `task-plan.json`,
`context-handoff.json`, `execution-result.json`, or `verification-result.json`
with an ad hoc Codex plan.

## Operating Principles

- For coding tasks, prefer Runner commands over manual procedure execution.
- Follow the Runner stage gate: scan/exploration -> intake -> spec -> plan ->
  execute -> verify.
- Prefer Runner-produced artifacts for stage state and handoff.
- Do not edit files, run build/test commands, or start implementation before
  Runner planning has produced `next_step: executor`.
- Read `.agents/logos/procedures/execution.md` only after the planning gate
  returns `next_step: executor`, or when Runner explicitly builds an execution
  prompt from it.
- Inspect before edits.
- Keep changes scoped to the user request.
- Plan before implementation.
- Review risk before sensitive or irreversible actions.
- Verify with concrete evidence before final response.
- Report skipped or unavailable checks plainly.

## Enforcement Boundary

Use `.agents/logos/procedures/review.md` as the source of truth for guard
enforcement status. Keep this file as routing guidance and put detailed
procedures in `.agents/logos/procedures/` and role boundaries in
`.agents/logos/roles/`.

## Work-State Recovery

Logos records low-cost work state under `.logos/`. Do not read
`.logos/runs/` or `.logos/evidence/` by default.

When continuing after context loss, compaction, or an unclear work state, read
`.logos/memory/resume-snapshot.md` first. If that is insufficient, read
`.logos/memory/active-work.json`, `.logos/memory/run-index.json`, and only then
the specific plan or run record needed. Raw evidence logs are for verification
or debugging, not routine context loading.

